criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adults with ventricular thrombus(VT), regardless of sex, basic diseases, occupation or
             education;

          -  The VT should be found newly within 3 months;

          -  The observational phase should last until the time that patients who had achieved
             thrombus resolution. The following up period after the phase ended should continue for
             at least 3 months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Individuals received standard antithrombotic therapy within 4 weeks;

          -  Individuals received the thrombectomy therapy, ventricular aneurysm resection or heart
             transplantation within 6 weeks since the VT was found in the first time;

          -  Had a long history of VT more than three months.
